/wiki/FC_Honka: FC Honka (also known as Esport Honka) is a Finnish football club, based in Espoo. It was promoted into the Finnish premier division (Veikkausliiga), for the first time in its history, at the end of the 2005 season. The club's manager is Vesa Vasara and it plays its home matches at Tapiolan urheilupuisto. It was founded in 1957 as Tapion Honka, and changed its name to FC Honka in 1975. FC Honka is largely renowned in Finland for its extensive youth scheme with over 1000 youth players playing in various age groups. It also has women's football team in the Naisten Liiga. Until 2005 FC Honka was thought of as a "nearly, but not quite" team, always underachieving in the Finnish First Division (Ykkönen). In the late 1990s the objective was promotion but year after year they failed.
/wiki/Ilves_FS: Ilves FS is a futsal club based in Tampere, Finland, part of multi-sport club Ilves. Ilves plays in the Futsal-Liiga, the top-division in Finnish futsal. Ilves is the most successful club in Futsal-Liiga with eight championships (most recent in 2013-2014).
/wiki/Tervarit: Tervarit is a football club based in Oulu, Finland. It plays currently in the Finnish third tier Kakkonen.
/wiki/Turun_Pallokerho:
Turun Pallokerho (or TPK) is an association football club from Turku, Finland currently playing in the Finnish fourth tier Kolmonen. TPK has played two seasons in the Finnish premier division Mestaruussarja in 1951 and 1952, finishing third in 1951.
 TPK is the first youth club of the Finland national football team goalkeeper Lukáš Hrádecký.
/wiki/Porin_Palloilijat: Porin Palloilijat or FC PoPa is a Finnish football club, based in the city of Pori in Finland. The club currently plays in the Ykkönen (First Division), the second highest level of Finnish football . The club was established in 1925 but did not operate between 1960 and 1981. It has been the leading football team in Pori since FC Jazz went bankrupt in early 2005.
/wiki/Sievi_Futsal:
FC YPA is a Finnish football club from the town of Ylivieska. FC YPA was formed in 1998. The club is currently playing in the Kakkonen, the third tier of the Finnish league system. FC YPA play their home matches at Safari.
 They also have a futsal team, Sievi Futsal.
/wiki/Someron_Voima: Someron Voima (abbreviated SoVo) is a sports club from Somero in Finland.  The club was formed in 1932 and their home ground is at the Someron urheilukenttä.  The men's football first team currently plays in the Kakkonen (Second Division).  The Chairman of SoVo is Timo Rannikko and Ismo Valve heads the Football Section.
/wiki/Futsal-Liiga: The Futsal-Liiga is the premier  futsal league in Finland.
